`,t.jsx(e.p,{children:"When an event is published to the event broker, the event Broker requires some metadata about the event that helps it decide where to route that event. This metadata is what we call Topics. Topics are hierarchical text strings that describes what’s in the event. Traditionally, the publisher publishes the event to a specific topic and the subscriber/consumer listens on a specific topic for events. In Redis Pub/Sub we refer to them as channels."}),`
`,t.jsx(e.p,{children:"This ensures that subscribers only recieve events that they need and also event brokers can effeciently and effectively route the events to the right intended consumers."}),`
