`,t.jsx(e.p,{children:"An event mesh is created and enabled through a network of interconnected event brokers. It’s a configurable and dynamic infrastructure layer for distributing events among decoupled applications, cloud services, and devices by dynamically routing events to any application, no matter where these applications are deployed in the world, in any cloud, on-premises, or IoT environment. Technically speaking, an event mesh is a network of interconnected event brokers that share consumer topic subscription information and route messages amongst themselves so they can be passed along to subscribers."}),`
